    aspect-ratio: 18 / 9;
}
}

@media screen and (min-width: 1200px) {
.wideframe {
    width: 1160px;
    aspect-ratio: 18 / 9;
    margin-left: calc(-580px + 50%);
    max-width: 1160px !important;
}
}

</style>
<div class="wideframe"><iframe style="border: none;" src="https://www.thinglink.com/view/scene/1844870031163261605" width="1200" height="581" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" data-original-width="2500" data-original-height="1213"></iframe><script async src="//cdn.thinglink.me/jse/responsive.js"></script></div>
<p><span class="wp-caption-text">First detected in 2020, clade 2.3.4.4b of avian flu was rapidly transmitted around the world. So far, 16 people have contracted the disease from animals. Infographic by Marina Wang and Mark Garrison</span></p>
<p>Unlike previous bird flu outbreaks, this pandemic has persisted for four years‚Äîeven through typically flu-free summers. The strain is also now circulating widely in Europe, Africa, and the Americas, where bird flu has not been endemic.</p>
<p>Another unusual feature of this bird flu pandemic has been its impact on mammals. This clade of H5N1 has infected foxes, sea lions, and even a polar bear. And the news has gotten even more grim: in February 2024, the virus reached mainland Antarctica and began tearing through the dense penguin colonies there. A month later, scientists found the virus spreading through dairy cow herds in the United States, and in April, virus fragments showed up in milk.</p>
<p>It‚Äôs unclear what risk‚Äîif any‚Äîinfected livestock pose for human health. So far, <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06631-2">clade 2.3.4.4b</a> has been found in 16 people who had close contact with infected poultry or cattle. The US <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/flu/avianflu/avian-flu-summary.htm">Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</a> reports that the risk of human infection is low. But scientists worry that each time the virus infects a new type of carrier‚Äîparticularly pigs, which host all kinds of flu strains‚Äîit has another opportunity to morph into a disease that will spread from human to human.</p>
				</section>

